@node features "Features"

  MultiView is complete replacement for standard C= MultiView with few new features :

  - fully working under OS 2.04 and higher
  - is fully localized (MV 39.xx isn't)
  - you can show file using external program or datatypes so you can forget
    setting misc tools for your icons - now you can set MultiView
  - multiselect in filerequesters and from Shell (C= MV can't do it)
  - inform you about filetype when recognize it
  - all configuration in program icon
  - external configuration program
  - can create appicon on WB - usage cannot be simplier !

  Full version of MultiView have few features more :

  - XFD Support - MV unpack file and check it one more time
  - you can define new filetypes - prefixes/suffixes
  - you can insert filename or filename with path in any part of command line
    (not only at end)
  - you can disable information requester

@endnode
@node intro "Introduction"


      When  I used OS 2.1 and unpack archives from Aminet, I often had this
situation :  doubleclick on an icon and a requester pops up :
@{i}@{FG shine}
              Unable to open your tool 'MultiView'
@{FG text}@{ui}
      So I search a Web for any MultiView like program for OS 2.x.  First I
get  mv2_x.lha  from Aminet dev/e and I see - it's not enough!  That proggy
check  filetype  by it's extension - this method is good only on pC but not
on  Amiga  so  i decided to write my own MultiView replacement.  But I need
something to identify filetypes by it's contents.  I found 2 libraries :

 - whatis.library 4.2 by Sylvain Rougier & Pierre Carrette
 - FileID.library 7.0 by BLOODROCK of SYNDICATE (now he is in TRSI)

      Whatis  is  hard  to configure for many filetypes and opening it take
too  much  time.  FileID 7.0 has 591 filetypes recognized without any other
files.  I include version 8.0 which knows 645 filetypes.

@endnode
@node "Installation" "Installation"

  To install MultiView you can use script for Installer. If you want do it
by hand you must copy requied libraries to LIBS: and main program to
SYS:Utilities.

@endnode
@node req "Requirements"

    MultiView 4.90 requirements are :

    - Real not emulated Amiga

    - OS 2.04 as minimum to work
    - OS 2.1  to have locale support
    - OS 3.0  for datatypes

    - libraries :

      FileID.library       v.2     (included)
      Asl.library          v.37    (part of AmigaOS)
      AmigaGuide.library   v.34    (for AmigaGuide files)
      AmigaGuide.library   v.39    (for datatypes support)
      datatypes.library    v.39
      Locale.library       v.38
      XFDMaster.library    v.38    (registered version only)

@endnode
@node Usage "Usage"

@{b} Running From Cli/Shell@{ub}

        MultiView FILE/M PUB=PUBSCREEN/K REQ=REQUESTER/S APPICON/S

           FILE      - if not present it will be file requester opened
           PUBSCREEN - if not present default screen will be used
           REQUESTER - always show info in requesters
           APPICON   - create appicon on WB

                     - others parameters will be ignored - they are added for
                       compability with MultiView by C=

@{b} Running From Workbench@{ub}

        1. Select one or more icons and double-click MultiView icon
        2. Double-click the program icon, and select files from the file
           requester to action.

@endnode
