@node works "How it works"

      How it works - step by step :

      1. Open program icon
      2. Get @{fg shine}SHOWINFO@{fg text} tooltype
      3. Check for OS 3.0
      4. Get filename from user
      5. Check filetype via @{b}FileId.library@{ub}
      6. Check filetype via @{b}datatypes.library@{ub}
      7. Get <filetype nr> tooltype
      8. Execute external program for that filetype or show it by
         @{b}AmigaGuide.library@{ub} when program is @{fg shine}DATATYPE@{fg text}
         If program can't open AmigaGuide.library then DEFAULT3 or DEFAULT
         will be used.

@endnode
@node Configuration "Configuration"

   There is MultiView Preferences program on Aminet:util/sys/2b_mv_prefs.lha.
Using this tool you can in easy way configure MultiView for your needs.

  Minimum configuration is no tooltypes. Then MultiView will work just like
old MultiView by C=.



   Starting from version 1.5 all configuration is saved in icon. Recognized
tooltypes are :

  @{fg shine}SHOWINFO@{fg text}    -> show info about filetype or no (YES|NO) - Default YES
                                      (registered version only)
  @{fg shine}DEFAULT@{fg text}     -> standard program (C:More)
  @{fg shine}DEFAULT3@{fg text}    -> standard program under OS 3.0+
  @{fg shine}DEF_MUSIC@{fg text}   -> stardard program for music files
  @{fg shine}DEF_GFX@{fg text}     -> stardard program for graphics files
  @{fg shine}DEF_EXE@{fg text}     -> stardard program for executables
  @{fg shine}DEF_PACKED@{fg text}  -> stardard program for packed files
  @{fg shine}DEF_ENCRYPT@{fg text} -> stardard program for crypted files
  @{fg shine}DEF_TEXT@{fg text}    -> stardard program for texts
  @{fg shine}DEF_IFF@{fg text}     -> stardard program for IFF files

      Configuration  for  filetype  isn't  simply.
  For FileID types you  must check filetype number  in  @{"filetypes" link "types" 0} list and wrote
tooltype number=program for this filetype.

  For DataTypes types you must get descriptor name and insert descriptor
name=program for this filetype.

  If you want to show file by datatypes you must define program as @{fg shine}DATATYPE@{fg text}.

@endnode
@node blabla "BlaBlaInfo"

   @{b}@{fg shine}BlaBla@{ub}@{fg text} is a Polish biggest system programmers group. We make the system
friendly programms. We guarantee that our programs will run on almost every
machine (@{fg fill}Amiga@{fg text} of course), including future ones. All our programs are
running in multitasking, and all of them are PD, Freeware, or Shareware.

   Our organisation has a few members (we "absorb" only good programmers),
an own e-mail address. Our newest productions you can find in our PD library
called "@{b}Polware@{ub}" or in Aminet - our archives always have names
stared "2b_". Our texts, articles you can also find in our disk-mag
"@{b}Izviestia@{ub}" (sorry, in Polish!).

   @{b}@{fg shine}BlaBla@{ub}@{fg text}  group  is  well-known  in Poland, and programs signed with
"Blabla"  are  for  sure very good. We made many productions, we help many
young  programmers, we write articles to Polish edition of @{b}Amiga Magazine@{ub},
@{i}we try to do all, for our beloved computer - Amiga!@{ui}

 Our InterNet HomePage     : @{b}http://www.blabla.w.pl@{ub}
 Our contact email address : @{b}blabla@zskl.p.lodz.pl@{ub}

@endnode
